      • graphicsDrawText

        public static final void graphicsDrawText(java.awt.Graphics2D g,
                                          String text,
                                          int x,
                                          int y,
                                          String face,
                                          boolean bold,
                                          boolean italic,
                                          int size,
                                          int horizontal,
                                          int vertical)
        Parameters:
        g -
        text -
        x -
        y -
        face -
        bold -
        italic -
        size -
        horizontal - specifies horizontal alignment of text box (by width), use:
        • 0 to have text aligned so its center point is in the given x coordinate;
        • use 1 (actually any integer value greater than zero) for left edge of the text box to be in the given x coordinate;
        • use -1 (actually any integer value less than zero) for right edge of the text box to be in the given x coordinate.
        vertical - specifies vertical alignment of text box (by height), use:
        • 0 to have text aligned so its center point is in the given y coordinate;
        • use 1 (actually any integer value greater than zero) for top edge of the text box to be in the given y coordinate;
        • use -1 (actually any integer value less than zero) for bottom edge of the text box to be in the given y coordinate.
